{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fund/legislate for improved security and facilities for HGV drivers",
        "additional_details": "Despite the essential role that HGV drivers play in keeping goods moving across the UK, we feel they often lack access to secure rest areas, well-lit truck stops, and sufficient CCTV coverage. Many are forced to park in unsafe locations due to a severe shortage of secure parking facilities, putting both drivers and cargo at risk. Cargo theft from HGVs is a growing problem, with over 5,370 thefts reported in 2023, resulting in direct losses of \u00a368.3 million.",
        "background": "We want the Government to:\r\n1 Invest in secure HGV parking facilities with fencing, lighting, CCTV, & security patrols\r\n2 Increase funding for roadside security measures at existing rest stops & laybys.\r\n3 Introduce specific freight crime legislation to ensure tougher penalties for organised theft",
